commit.message:
C99 compatibility fixes

Add a prototypes for the strlcpy, strlcat functions, to avoid an
implicit function declaration, via the string-compat.h header file.
Otherwise, the package will fail to build with future compilers which
no longer support implicit function declarations by default.  Include
"string-compat.h" in the source files that call strlcpy or strlcat.

Include <sys/queue.h> to scanssh.h, so that the TAILQ_HEAD macro is
defined.  Otherwise “TAILQ_HEAD(socksq, socks_host);“ is parsed as
a declaration of a function called TAILQ_HEAD, with implicit ints.

md5.c calls memset and memcpy, so include <string.h> for the
prototypes.

Remove Semaphore CI

Semaphore CI currently not used.
